value.value: An ependymal tumor that occurs during childhood.

Human TUBA1B wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 12q13.12 and is approximately 4 kb in length. This allele, which encodes tubulin alpha-1B chain protein, is involved in microtubule dynamics.
Tubulin alpha-1B chain (451 aa, ~50 kDa) is encoded by the human TUBA1B gene. This protein plays a role in microtubule structure.
A mixed glioma that occurs during childhood.
A pineal parenchymal cell neoplasm that occurs during childhood.
A carrier of a mutation in BRCA1 gene.
A carrier of a mutation in BRCA2 gene.
Any heart or vascular disorder occurring as a consequence of injury to the cardiovascular system.

An antineoplastic oligosaccharide anthracycline antineoplastic antibiotic isolated from the bacterium Actinosporangium bohemicum.  Marcellomycin intercalates into DNA and induces DNA crosslinks, thereby inhibiting DNA replication and repair and RNA and protein synthesis.  This agent also induces differentiation in HL-60 promyelocytic leukemia cells by interfering with glycoprotein synthesis. (NCI04)
Castleman disease that presents with localized lymphadenopathy.
A cerebellar anaplastic astrocytoma that occurs during childhood.
A cerebral anaplastic astrocytoma that occurs during childhood.

label.value: Childhood Embryonal Tumor with Multilayered Rosettes, C19MC-Altered

value.value: An embryonal tumor with multilayered rosettes, C19MC-altered that occurs during childhood.
Grade III lymphomatoid granulomatosis that occurs during childhood.
A finding of childhood pineoblastoma that has not been treated.

label.value: Cognitive Side Effects of Cancer Therapy

value.value: Cognitive impairment caused by cancer treatment.

A rare, autosomal recessive inherited disorder caused by mutation in the c-Mpl gene.  It is characterized by thrombocytopenia and absence of megakaryocytes.  It presents with bleeding in the first month of life.

label.value: Crohn Disease-Associated Dysplasia of the Colorectum

value.value: A morphologic finding indicating the presence of dysplastic epithelial changes in an intestinal tissue sample that is affected by Crohn disease.
Any skin disorder occurring as a consequence of injury to the skin tissue.
A carcinoma that arises from the distal part of the urethra.
Germ cell tumor that arises from the testis and is diagnosed in at least two relatives.
Waldenstrom macroglobulinemia in a patient who has at least one first degree relative with either Waldenstrom macroglobulinemia or another B-cell lymphoproliferative disorder.
Temperature elevation, sweating, and red flushed face.
Any disorder of the organs of the digestive system occurring as a consequence of injury to the digestive system.

A natural killer T-cell subtype bearing an invariant T-cell receptor. Invariant natural killer T-cells recognize a small variety of glycolipid antigens presented in the context of CD1d. These cells play a regulatory role during an immune response by producing cytokines.

A T-cell subtype bearing a semi-invariant T-cell receptor and restricted by the major histocompatibility complex related molecule MR1. These cells occupy peripheral tissues and are noted for their reactivity against various microorganisms of either bacterial or fungal origin.

A laboratory test to determine the presence or absence of SH2 domain-containing protein 1A (SLAM-associated protein, SAP) expression. Loss of SAP expression is associated with X-linked lymphoproliferative syndrome 1.
A human hair color characterized by low levels of eumelanin.
A human skin color characterized by low levels of eumelanin.
A coagulation disorder characterized by a tendency for excessive bleeding.
Indicates that a person's current status of health is not known.
Indicates that a donor of stem cells is healthy.
Any disorder of the liver occurring as a consequence of injury to the liver parenchyma.
Genetic inheritance of neuroblastoma caused by mutations in the ALK or PHOX2B genes.  Familial neuroblastomas have a higher incidence of multiple primary tumors and are diagnosed at an earlier age.

value.value: Side effects of cancer treatment occurring a long time after the treatment was completed.

A question about a person's most important health issues.

A response indicating that an individual has or had no change in their appearance.
